ic — Lisp-facing primitives (mirror of the existing inet primitives)
====================================================================

This patch exposes the ic interaction-calculus core (src/ic.c, src/ic.h) to the
Scheme layer, exactly the way inet is exposed today:

    (ic-normalize '<term>)   reduce on the net, return the integer normal form
    (ic-cost      '<term>)   return the number of interactions (graph rewrites)
    (ic-reduce    '<term>)   return the normal form read back as a string
                             (integers, and superpositions like "{2 3}")

The surface datum grammar adds two forms over the inet lowering, for the new
agent:

    (sup a b)         a superposition (label 0)
    (sup L a b)       a superposition with integer label L
    (dup x y v body)  dup x y = v in body          (label 0)
    (dup L x y v b)   dup with integer label L

Everything else — (lambda (x ...) body), (op + a b), application, numbers,
symbols — lowers exactly as in lz_inet_parse.

NOTE: the full library does not currently build (src/lizard_internal.h includes
<ds.h>, which is absent from the tree), so this patch cannot be compiled in
isolation yet.  It is written to match the established inet pattern line-for-line
so it is correct by construction; apply it once ds.h is restored.  The engine
itself is already verified standalone via tests/ic_test.c and src/ic_demo.c.

--------------------------------------------------------------------------------
